---
import ButtonizedLink from "@components/ButtonizedLink.astro";

const name:String = 'Dasandimian';
---
<!-- pls button hello world -->
<p>These sends API request to our Netlify functions <code>hello-world</code> with argument <code>name</code> filled with whatever name you like</p>
<p>URL = <code>{Astro.url.origin}/api/hello-world?name=YOUR_NAME</code></p>
<h3>Fixed Button</h3>
<ButtonizedLink href={`/api/hello-world?name=${name}`}>Hello, {name}</ButtonizedLink>
<h3>Customize</h3>
<form action='/api/hello-world' method='GET'>
    <label for="name">Enter your Name:</label>
    <input type='text' name='name' id='name'/>
    <br/>
    <input type='submit' value="Submit"/>
</form>
<p>
    NOTE: The method must be <b><code>GET</code></b> so it will processed using URL Parameters (<code>?name=YOUR_NAME&amp;desc=DESCRIPTIONS</code>, that Question mark followed with variables) above.<br/>
    We haven't yet figured how to process <code>POST</code> method at the moment.
</p>